quran[27]{c,v,t}:
  10,26,"Those who are virtuous shall receive the best reward and an enhancement. Neither dust nor abasement shall overcast their faces. They shall be the inhabitants of paradise, and they shall remain in it [forever]"
  10,27,"For those who have committed misdeeds, the requital of a misdeed shall be its like, and they shall be overcast by abasement. They shall have no one to protect [them] from Allah. [They will be] as if their faces were covered with dark patches of the night. They shall be the inmates of the Fire, and they shall remain in it [forever]"
  10,28,"On the day when We gather them all together, We shall say to those who ascribe partners [to Allah], ‘Stay where you are—you and your partners!’ Then We shall set them apart from one another, and their partners will say, ‘It was not us that you worshipped"
  10,29,Allah suffices as a witness between you and us. We were indeed unaware of your worship.’
  10,30,"There every soul will examine what it has sent in advance, and they will be returned to Allah, their real master, and what they used to fabricate will forsake them"
  10,31,"Say, ‘Who provides for you out of the sky and the earth? Who controls [your] hearing and sight, and who brings forth the living from the dead and brings forth the dead from the living, and who directs the command?’ They will say, ‘Allah.’ Say, ‘Will you not then be wary [of Him]?’"
  10,32,"That, then, is Allah, your true Lord. So what is there after the truth except error? Then where are you being led away"
  10,33,"Thus the word of your Lord became due against those who transgress, that they shall not have faith"
  10,34,"Say, ‘Is there anyone among your partners who originates the creation and then brings it back?’ Say, ‘Allah originates the creation, then He will bring it back.’ Then where do you stray"
  10,35,"Say, ‘Is there anyone among your partners who may guide to the truth?’ Say, ‘Allah guides to the truth. Is He who guides to the truth worthier to be followed, or he who is not guided unless shown the way? What is the matter with you? How do you judge?’"
  10,36,Most of them just follow conjecture; indeed conjecture is no substitute for the truth. Indeed Allah knows best what they do
  10,37,"This Quran could not have been fabricated by anyone besides Allah; rather, it is a confirmation of what was [revealed] before it, and an elaboration of the Book, there is no doubt in it, from the Lord of all the worlds"
  10,38,"Do they say, ‘He has fabricated it?’ Say, ‘Then bring a surah like it, and invoke whomever you can, besides Allah, should you be truthful.’"
  10,39,"Indeed, they deny something whose knowledge they do not comprehend, and whose explanation has not yet come to them. Those who were before them denied likewise. So observe how was the fate of the wrongdoers"
  10,40,"Some of them believe in it, and some of them do not believe in it, and your Lord best knows the agents of corruption"
  10,41,"If they deny you, say, ‘My deeds belong to me and your deeds belong to you: you are absolved of what I do and I am absolved of what you do.’"
  10,42,There are some of them who prick up their ears at you. But can you make the deaf hear even if they do not exercise their reason
  10,43,There are some of them who observe you. But can you guide the blind even if they do not perceive
  10,44,"Indeed Allah does not wrong people in the least; rather, it is people who wrong themselves"
  10,45,"On the day He will gather them [it will be] as if they had not remained [in the world] except for an hour of the day getting acquainted with one another. They are certainly losers who deny the encounter with Allah, and they are not guided"
  10,46,"Whether We show you a part of what We promise them, or take you away [before that], [in any case] their return will be to Us and Allah will be witness to what they do"
  10,47,"There is an apostle for every nation; so when their apostle comes, judgement is made between them with justice, and they are not wronged"
  10,48,"They say, ‘When will this promise be fulfilled, should you be truthful?’"
  10,49,"Say, ‘I have no control over any benefit for myself nor [over] any harm except what Allah may wish. There is a time for every nation: when their time comes, they shall not defer it by a single hour nor shall they advance it.’"
  10,50,"Say, ‘Tell me, should His punishment overtake you by night or day, [you will not be able to avert it]; so what part of it do the guilty seek to hasten?’"
  10,51,"‘What! Do you believe it when it has befallen? Now? While you would seek to hasten it [earlier]?!’"
  10,52,"Then it will be said to those who were wrongdoers, ‘Taste the everlasting punishment. Shall you not be requited for what you used to earn?’"